    Programming 101

• Think about problem
• Type out solution
• Debug

--

    Debugging

• Figure out why the code is broken
• Fix the code
• Repeat. (lots)

--

    puts

• Easy to use
• Can check one hypothesis
• Inefficient

--

    binding.pry

• Quite easy to use (`gem install pry`, `require pry`)
• Can check multiple hypotheses
• More efficient

--
    
    pry-rescue

• Somewhat easy to use (`gem install pry-rescue`, `rescue <program>`)
• Can check multiple hypotheses
• Super-efficient

--

    NoMethodError

• Typo 
• Calling the wrong function on the right object
• Calling the right function on the wrong object

--

    edit --ex

• Opens your editor
• Jumps to the problem
• Reloads the code

--

    ls --grep

• Finds the right function
• Much faster than Google/ri/rdoc
• Can use show-doc/show-source for more detail

--

    up/down

• Move pry up and down the callstack
• Discover why you have the wrong object
• Debug gems

--

    And more...

• Try `help` inside Pry
• wtf? 
• Loads of plugins: gem list -r 'pry-*'

